# How I grouped these and why

* **Pure-play AI drug-discovery platforms** (e.g., Recursion, Exscientia, SchrÃ¶dinger, Relay, AbCellera): *direct exposure* to the success of AI-designed molecules and platform licensing.
* **Large pharm (e.g., Lilly, Pfizer, Novo, Moderna, BioNTech)**: *deep pockets + ability to scale* â€” theyâ€™ll commercialize successful AI-enabled programs and can buy small AI leaders.
* **Platform & infra providers (NVIDIA, CROs, synthetic-biology foundries)**: they are *indirect but powerful* financial plays because the whole sector needs compute, data pipelines, and lab automation.
* **Watchlist / IPO candidates**: many of the most interesting pure-play AI companies are still private or have recently changed status â€” these are high upside but require checking current listing status before investing.

